    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A process of weaving in which each weft thread always passes alternately over then under every successive warp thread.  Both sides of such weaving are structurally identical.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000132/Suzzallo-UW</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000013591/Emery, Primary Structure of Fabrics (1980)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een weefprocedé waarbij iedere inslagdraad altijd afwisselend over en onder elke volgende kettingdraad loopt. Beide zijden van dergelijke weefsels hebben dezelfde structuur.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種紡織過程，每條緯線與經線上下交錯編入，因此織布的兩面皆有相同結構。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
